The event \(|X - \mu| < d\) with \(d = 0.05\) is considered. The value \(k\) is given by \(k = d / \sigma\), where \(\sigma = \sqrt{0.000375} \approx 0.019365\). Thus, \(k \approx 0.05 / 0.019365 \approx 2.581\), and \(k^2 \approx 6.659561\). Then, \(1/k^2 \approx 0.1501\), and the lower bound is \(1 - 0.1501 = 0.8499\).

