- The percentage with an irregular heartbeat is 17%.
- Of those with an irregular heartbeat, 35% have high blood pressure, so the percentage with both irregular heartbeat and high blood pressure is 35% × 17% = 5.95%.
- Of those with normal blood pressure, 11% have an irregular heartbeat, so the percentage with both irregular heartbeat and normal blood pressure is 11% × 65% = 7.15%.
- The total percentage with an irregular heartbeat is the sum of those with irregular heartbeat and high, normal, or low blood pressure: 5.95% + 7.15% + percentage with irregular heartbeat and low blood pressure = 17%.
- Solving for the percentage with irregular heartbeat and low blood pressure: 17% - 5.95% - 7.15% = 3.90%.
