Solution: The sample mean \(\bar{X}\) for a random sample of size \(n = 12\) from a uniform distribution on \((0,1)\) has a population mean \(\mu = 0.5\) and population variance \(\sigma^2 = \frac{1}{12}\). By the Central Limit Theorem, \(\bar{X}\) is approximately normally distributed with mean \(\mu_{\bar{X}} = 0.5\) and variance \(\sigma_{\bar{X}}^2 = \frac{\sigma^2}{n} = \frac{1/12}{12} = \frac{1}{144}\), so the standard deviation is \(\sigma_{\bar{X}} = \frac{1}{12}\).

